 type="html">Pi 0.64.0 is documented</title><link href="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/31/Pi.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pi 0.64.0 is documented" /><published>2026-03-31T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-31T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/31/Pi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/31/Pi.html"></content><author><name>Jinghua Zhao</name><email>jinghuazhao@hotmail.com</email></author><category term="info" /><category term="AI" /><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">R is documented</title><link href="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/16/R.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="R is documented" /><published>2026-03-16T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-16T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/16/R</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/16/R.html">&lt;p&gt;See &amp;lt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/applications/R.html&quot;&gt;https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/applications/R.html&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;05052026&quot;&gt;05/05/2026&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current version is 4.6.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;16032026&quot;&gt;16/03/2026&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current version is 4.5.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The series include R/4.5.3-icelake, R/4.5.3-gcc11, R/4.5.3-gcc12.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Since R_LIBS has R, R-gcc11/R-gcc12 those in their respective directories are recognised automattically.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;In the case of R/4.5.3-gcc12, a fully functional gcc/12.5.0 is made, &lt;a href=&quot;https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/systems/setup.html#fn:gcc&quot;&gt;https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/systems/setup.html#fn:gcc&lt;/a&gt;.
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;There might be some residuals from using -lintl, therefore xgboost is experimented with LIBS=”-lintl”.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;The issue goes away with gcc/12.5.0.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><author><name>Jinghua Zhao</name><email>jinghuazhao@hotmail.com</email></author><category term="info" /><summary type="html">See &amp;lt; https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/applications/R.html&amp;gt; 05/05/2026 The current version is 4.6.0. 16/03/2026 The current version is 4.5.3. Note that, The series include R/4.5.3-icelake, R/4.5.3-gcc11, R/4.5.3-gcc12. Since R_LIBS has R, R-gcc11/R-gcc12 those in their respective directories are recognised automattically. In the case of R/4.5.3-gcc12, a fully functional gcc/12.5.0 is made, https://cambridge-ceu.github.io/csd3/systems/setup.html#fn:gcc. There might be some residuals from using -lintl, therefore xgboost is experimented with LIBS=”-lintl”. The issue goes away with gcc/12.5.0.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">OpenClaw 2026.3.8 is documented</title><link href="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/11/openclaw.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="OpenClaw 2026.3.8 is documented" /><published>2026-03-11T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-11T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/11/openclaw</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/11/openclaw.html"></content><author><name>Jinghua Zhao</name><email>jinghuazhao@hotmail.com</email></author><category term="info" /><category term="AI" /><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">gaawr2 0.0.7 is published on CRAN</title><link href="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/10/gaawr2.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="gaawr2 0.0.7 is published on CRAN" /><published>2026-03-10T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-10T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/10/gaawr2</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://jinghuazhao.github.io/2026/03/10/gaawr2.html">&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jinghuazhao.github.io/gaawr2/index.html&quot;&gt;https://jinghuazhao.github.io/gaawr2/index.html&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

